        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 10:55PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1054 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Towner to near Coolidge. These storms were
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holly, Hartman, and Towner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
